17. Supplemental U.S. State Notice
This Supplemental U.S. State Notice applies exclusively to visitors and users of the ecobee Services who reside in certain U.S. states with comprehensive privacy laws, such as California, Colorado, Connecticut, Virginia, or Utah. This section is intended to satisfy our requirements under those states’ respective privacy laws (collectively, “State Privacy Laws”).
Notice at Collection.
The following sub-sections below, read together, are intended to comply with our obligations for Notice at Collection under the California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”):
“
Categories of Personal Information We May Collect, Disclose, or Sell/Share”, “Purposes of Collection, Use, and Disclosure”
, and “
Retention
”.
Scope.
This section applies to “personal information”, or “personal data” as defined under State Privacy Laws, whether collected online or offline, in our capacity as a business or controller. This section does not address or apply to our handling of publicly available information or personal information that is otherwise exempt under State Privacy Laws. This section also does not apply to personal information we collect about job applicants, independent contractors, or current or former full-time, part-time and temporary employees and staff, officers, directors or owners of ecobee; different notices apply.
Categories of Personal Information We May Collect, Disclose, or Sell/Share.
Click here
to view information about the categories of personal information that we may collect and disclose to others for a business or commercial purpose (and have collected/disclosed in the prior 12-months), and information about our “selling” and “sharing” of personal information.
State Privacy Laws such as the CCPA define “sale” as disclosing or making available personal information to a third party in exchange for monetary (or other valuable) consideration. The CCPA defines “sharing” as disclosing or making available personal information to a third party for purposes of cross-context behavioral advertising, whereas other State Privacy Laws consider this to be “Targeted Advertising.”  We may be considered to be “selling” or “sharing” personal information solely because of our use of third-party advertising and analytics cookies and tools on our Websites and because of our disclosure of certain ecobee Product user data to third parties for their own marketing purposes.  Please note that we do not sell or share personal information about individuals we know are under sixteen.
