1. YOU MUST BE ELIGIBLE TO ENTER THESE TOS
The Remote Applications are offered and available to individuals who are 18 years of age or older and eligible to use the Remote Applications. By accessing or using the Remote Applications, you represent and warrant that you are 18 years of age or older and eligible to use the Remote Applications.
2. ecobee Account
In order to use the Remote Applications, you must have or set up an account with ecobee (“ecobee Account”).
ecobee reserves the right, in ecobee’s sole discretion, to reject any registration for an ecobee Account.
As part of the ecobee Account set-up process, you will be asked to provide certain personal information. ecobee will only use such personal information in accordance with the terms of Section 4 below.
If you choose to set-up an ecobee Account, then you agree to: (i) provide true, accurate, current, and complete information; (ii) maintain and promptly update the information you provide to ecobee; and (iii) not to provide any irrelevant data into any form or data entry field other than the data requested by ecobee for such field. In the event that you provide, or ecobee reasonably suspects that you have provided, any information that is untrue, inaccurate, not current, or incomplete, then ecobee has the right to suspend or terminate your ecobee Account and refuse any and all current or future use of the Remote Applications.
Your ecobee Account username and password (“Login Methods”) are solely for your use or the use of the entity or person you represent. You are solely responsible for the confidentiality and security of your Login Methods. You are responsible for all activities that occur under your ecobee Account. ecobee is not obligated to inquire as to the authority or propriety of any use of, or action taken under, your Login Methods and/or ecobee Account.
3. Utility Account
eco+ works by monitoring your energy use, the usage rate structure of your utility provider and any Community Energy Savings Programs (as defined below) that your utility provider (“Utility”), Regional Transmission Organization, Independent System Operator, state agency, or third-party partners or implementors of such programs may issue (with your Utility, individually or collectively, “Program Administrators”).
In order to gain the full benefits of eco+, you must have an account with your Utility (“Utility Account”) or have the permission of the Utility Account owner to enter into these TOS. To achieve the full benefits of eco+, you also need to allow eco+ to connect to such Utility Account and share data with such Utility Account, as is described in Section 4 below.
In order to enable your use of eco+, you affirmatively direct ecobee to share your personal information with Program Administrators as necessary to implement the Community Energy Savings Programs. Additionally, you affirmatively consent to the release of your Utility Account data by your Utility to ecobee and other Program Administrators. In some jurisdictions, additional measures may be required by law or by your Utility in order for your Utility to recognize your consent to the release of your Utility Account data. You acknowledge that you understand that if you do not consent to the release of your Utility Account data by your Utility to ecobee and other Program Administrators, ecobee may be unable to provide certain eco+ features to you and you may not realize the full benefit of eco+.
You agree to: (i) provide true, accurate, current, and complete information regarding your Utility Account; (ii) maintain and promptly update the information you provide to ecobee; and (iii) not to provide any irrelevant data into any form or data entry field other than the data requested by ecobee for such field. In the event that you provide, or ecobee reasonably suspects that you have provided, any information that is untrue, inaccurate, not current, or incomplete, then ecobee has the right to suspend or terminate your use of eco+ and refuse any and all current or future use of eco+.
4. Privacy Policy and Data Sharing
ecobee is committed to protecting your privacy. Please review our Privacy Policy, located at ecobee.com/en-ca/privacy-policy, to understand how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information gathered by the Remote Applications.
In order to operate and make eco+ available, ecobee collects, and may disclose, your personal information to Program Administrators, and Program Administrators may disclose your personal information to us. Under ecobee’s Privacy Policy, which is incorporated into these TOS by reference, eco+ is defined as a “Utility Program.” Utility Programs may include both Community Energy Savings Programs and other energy efficiency programs. Your privacy is important to ecobee, and ecobee’s Privacy Policy explains how ecobee collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal information. Subject to any applicable law, your personal information may be used to assess your eligibility to participate in Utility Programs; verify your participation in Utility Programs; assist in decision making relating to energy production, grid stability, and conservation; and provide demand response, energy measurement, and verification services to a Program Administrator or its governing regulatory body. ecobee may also use the information to improve the ecobee Services and Remote Applications.
Disabling eco+ will revoke your consent and terminate ecobee’s ability to share further personal information with Program Administrators.
5. Community Energy Savings Programs
When you activate eco+,  you will automatically be enrolled in demand response programs and events initiated by Program Administrators relating to grid stabilization or demand management (“Default Community Energy Savings Programs”). These programs reduce energy consumption and load on the grid, reducing costs and the risks of brownouts and blackouts. You can opt out of participation in any and all Default Community Energy Savings Programs and their events at any time by deactivating the Default Community Energy Savings Program in the ecobee App, by contacting ecobee Customer Service at 1-877-932-6233, or by indefinitely deactivating eco+ within the ecobee App in the eco+ menu.
You may be eligible to participate in additional demand response programs offered by Program Administrators, which may require you to accept additional terms and conditions and may offer you incentives for enrolling and participating in the program (“Additional Community Energy Savings Programs,” and together with Default Community Energy Savings Programs, “Community Energy Savings Programs”). In such cases, eco+ will seek to notify you of these third-party terms and conditions and allow you to opt into such Additional Community Energy Savings Programs. If you enroll into an Additional Community Energy Savings Program, you may receive notice of Additional Community Energy Savings Program events which will appear on your ecobee Product and ecobee App. Note that if you opt in and enroll in an Additional Community Energy Savings Program, you will automatically be unenrolled from any Default Community Energy Savings Program. You can opt out of any in progress Additional Community Energy Savings Program event at any time, notwithstanding any clauses to the contrary set forth in your Utility’s terms and conditions, by deactivating the Additional Community Energy Savings Program in the ecobee App and submitting a request to the Program Administrator to unenroll.
ecobee does not determine customer eligibility for Community Energy Savings Programs. Those determinations are made solely by Program Administrators and are outside of ecobee’s control.
6. Specific Acknowledgements by You
You acknowledge and agree that:
a. ecobee may manage and control your ecobee Product(s) in order to provide eco+ and in order for you to participate in Community Energy Savings Programs;
b. If you do not opt out of the Default Community Energy Savings Program, ecobee may manage and control your ecobee Products during periods of peak energy demand for the grid, which may or may not coincide with peak electricity price periods;
c. ecobee may manage and control your ecobee Product(s) in order to provide additional energy savings when it provides value to Program Administrators or the electricity grid, such as during periods of high electricity demand;
d. You authorize and direct ecobee to share your personal information with Program Administrators to the extent necessary in order to provide the eco+ service and facilitate the Community Energy Savings Programs;
e. The Program Administrator may issue requests for reducing your energy consumption during Community Energy Savings Programs events, such as during peak electricity price periods. During these Community Energy Savings Program events, ecobee may change your temperature set point (for Default Community Energy Savings Programs) or turn off your ecobee Product(s) (for Additional Community Energy Savings Programs). However, you can always override ecobee’s control of your ecobee Product(s) and manually control your affected ecobee Product(s);
f. The Program Administrator may offer programs and offer incentives for you to participate in Additional Community Energy Savings Programs. In some cases, you may need to accept additional terms in order to participate in one of these Additional Community Energy Savings Programs. Participation in an Additional Community Energy Savings Program is optional. ecobee will communicate with you the details of the Additional Community Energy Savings Program, including how to participate or opt out. However, ecobee is not responsible for any failure on the part of the Program Administrator to provide any incentives to you;
g. ecobee may receive consideration from the Program Administrator for successfully enrolling you in eco+ programs
1
. So long as it does not conflict with any incentives provided to you under S.6(f)., ecobee shall be eligible to claim any qualifying environmental attributes, benefits, credits, awards or bounties from Program Administrators resulting from savings gained by the benefit of eco+, which forfeits any option you might have to enroll in the programs directly or rights to environmental attributes related to eco+;
h. ecobee may communicate with you via email with respect to the ecobee Products and Services and Remote Applications. For example, by registering your device and providing an email address during the account creation process, ecobee may from time to time send you HVAC alerts and reminders, notices about software updates, energy savings advice, news about ecobee Services, customer feedback or surveys, as well as marketing materials related to ecobee and other third-party product offerings. These electronic communications may be sent through email, the ecobee Website, the ecobee App, or other communication channels as deemed relevant by ecobee. You may unsubscribe from these emails at any time;
i. Without limiting the disclaimers in Section 9, ecobee makes no representations, warranties, or guarantees regarding any results of or performance of eco+, including that eco+ will achieve any energy saving or other benefits for you. Although unlikely, in rare circumstances, eco+ could potentially result in increased costs.
